lead_paragraph: Jamaican sprinter Elaine Thompson and 400 metre hurdler Janieve Russell have been given until Aug. 8 to prove their fitness for the Rio Olympics after getting medical exemptions from the national trials, team bosses said.

headline.print_headline: Jamaican Medal Contenders Given Week to Prove Fitness
